other_tests.findings: The liver parenchyma is normal without focal lesions. Multiple mobile nonobstructing gallstones are seen. There is no evidence of acute cholecystitis. Murphy sign is negative. There is no intra- or extra-hepatic biliary dilatation with the common bile duct measuring 5 mm. The pancreas is partially visualized and normal. There is no free fluid. Portal vein is patent with normal hepatopetal flow.
